\par An interesting revelation brought about by these two plots is that while those older seem to be less likely to be bothered by a baby being on a flight, they are more likely to be upset by an unruly child.

\section*{Conclusion}


\par After exploring the data a bit more, it is clear that there are wide ranges of what passengers perceive to be acceptable behavior on an airplane.
